1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:02,020
(Previously)
This is Lynx, my boyfriend.

2
00:00:02,713 --> 00:00:05,699
I'm sorry for not being
honest with you earlier.

3
00:00:06,244 --> 00:00:07,930
I understand you all did it

4
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:09,403
because you were worried about me.

5
00:00:09,663 --> 00:00:13,009
All this time, I just
wanted to see you happy.

6
00:00:13,443 --> 00:00:14,686
And today, I finally did.

7
00:00:15,148 --> 00:00:17,912
I think you're ready
now to take this power.

8
00:00:18,286 --> 00:00:20,888
Why do I still only hear "Meow"?

9
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:23,378
She said… she just
remembered something important.

10
00:00:23,421 --> 00:00:27,905
But if I had to pass it
on, it'd have to be… Leo.

11
00:00:28,010 --> 00:00:29,989
So in the end, I was never
the one you chose, Mom.

12
00:00:30,013 --> 00:00:33,533
6 MONTHS EARLIER

13
00:01:06,156 --> 00:01:07,156
Mom,

14
00:01:09,389 --> 00:01:10,905
when you first opened this café,

15
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:13,684
were you able to sleep?

16
00:01:15,517 --> 00:01:16,525
Of course, you were.

17
00:01:19,114 --> 00:01:20,511
You were never afraid of anything.

18
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:22,621
If there was one thing you were afraid of,

19
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:25,090
it would be me
taking over this café from you, right?

20
00:01:26,808 --> 00:01:28,317
Hey, Granny Juu.

21
00:01:29,103 --> 00:01:30,103
How did you get in here?

22
00:01:35,218 --> 00:01:36,218
Hm?

23
00:01:39,916 --> 00:01:40,917
Your whisker?

24
00:01:42,787 --> 00:01:43,792
Thank you, Granny.

25
00:01:45,794 --> 00:01:47,248
Mom sent you to help me, didn't she?

26
00:01:48,534 --> 00:01:50,312
I'll save it for when I truly need it.

27
00:01:55,857 --> 00:01:58,913
PRESENT DAY

28
00:01:59,058 --> 00:02:00,058
Meow.

29
00:02:08,188 --> 00:02:09,877
Are you worried about me after last night?

30
00:02:10,140 --> 00:02:14,012
But if I had to pass it on,
it'd have to be…

31
00:02:19,709 --> 00:02:20,709
Leo.

32
00:02:22,705 --> 00:02:24,198
That's actually good to know, Granny.

33
00:02:25,618 --> 00:02:27,404
So I know what Mom really wanted.

34
00:02:36,383 --> 00:02:37,383
Granny Juu.

35
00:02:42,995 --> 00:02:44,207
Can you look after Leo for me?

36
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:44,000
"Cat For Cash"
(Episode 10)

37
00:03:46,043 --> 00:03:47,077
Did you get hold of Lynx?

38
00:03:48,415 --> 00:03:51,487
He hadn't come down yet,
so I went up to his room

39
00:03:51,734 --> 00:03:53,501
and all I found was
the key and this note.

40
00:04:00,426 --> 00:04:02,826
LEO, TAKE CARE OF MOM'S CAFÉ FOR ME.

41
00:04:04,266 --> 00:04:06,504
What's this about? I don't get it.

42
00:04:08,033 --> 00:04:09,033
Well…

43
00:04:11,368 --> 00:04:12,397
we just found out

44
00:04:13,937 --> 00:04:16,087
that Je Meow intended to
hand this café over to you.

45
00:04:18,545 --> 00:04:19,998
I once joked with Mom

46
00:04:21,857 --> 00:04:23,558
that if she couldn't run the café anymore,

47
00:04:24,092 --> 00:04:25,205
I'd take it over.

48
00:04:26,376 --> 00:04:29,107
Then one day she actually called

49
00:04:29,407 --> 00:04:30,813
and said she'd give the cafe to me.

50
00:04:34,028 --> 00:04:35,028
At first,

51
00:04:36,829 --> 00:04:38,107
I thought she was kidding,

52
00:04:40,063 --> 00:04:41,128
but it was actually…

53
00:04:44,178 --> 00:04:45,618
her farewell call.

54
00:04:58,216 --> 00:04:59,216
Mom…

55
00:05:00,002 --> 00:05:01,810
Lynx has done such a
good job with this café.

56
00:05:03,988 --> 00:05:05,683
I don't think I could ever fill his shoes.

57
00:05:08,512 --> 00:05:13,307
No one is more suited
to run this café than Lynx.

58
00:05:22,213 --> 00:05:23,213
Well then…

59
00:05:25,403 --> 00:05:26,603
let's go find Lynx together.

60
00:05:30,576 --> 00:05:31,616
- Granny Juu!
- Granny Juu!

61
00:05:38,354 --> 00:05:40,185
It looks like it's what we were afraid of.

62
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:42,367
What's wrong with her?

63
00:05:47,749 --> 00:05:48,761
The other day,

64
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,115
I took Granny Juu in for a heart checkup.

65
00:05:52,087 --> 00:05:54,930
They said she wasn't doing well.

66
00:05:56,588 --> 00:05:58,994
Why didn't you tell us something this important?

67
00:05:59,155 --> 00:06:00,413
How was I supposed to tell you?

68
00:06:01,076 --> 00:06:02,996
You two were stressed about
your mom at the time.

69
00:06:03,826 --> 00:06:04,826
Don't worry.

70
00:06:05,278 --> 00:06:06,923
Granny Juu is breathing normally again.

71
00:06:08,591 --> 00:06:11,206
Let's see if her condition will get better.

72
00:06:11,699 --> 00:06:14,714
(Lynx… where are you, Lynx?)

73
00:06:43,071 --> 00:06:45,806
How did you know that I'd be here?

74
00:06:48,551 --> 00:06:50,026
I just hope that our café's cats

75
00:06:51,564 --> 00:06:53,008
would wander back here again.

76
00:06:54,864 --> 00:06:57,518
Jiro, let's go home.

77
00:06:57,905 --> 00:07:00,312
Jiro, come out already.

78
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:02,710
That day, I thought I made my mom proud.

79
00:07:05,952 --> 00:07:08,730
The truth is, she had probably stopped
waiting for me a long time ago.

80
00:07:09,991 --> 00:07:11,311
Don't be mad at her.

81
00:07:13,050 --> 00:07:14,103
I just regret it.

82
00:07:17,811 --> 00:07:19,725
If I had shown up that day
when Mom asked me to,

83
00:07:22,046 --> 00:07:24,297
we could have sat down together
over Korat fried noodles,

84
00:07:25,012 --> 00:07:26,076
talked things through,

85
00:07:29,624 --> 00:07:31,224
and I could have helped her at the café.

86
00:07:35,892 --> 00:07:37,101
All I can do now is…

87
00:07:40,122 --> 00:07:42,110
hold on to the blanket
that still has her scent.

88
00:07:48,505 --> 00:07:49,505
Lynx.

89
00:07:55,741 --> 00:07:57,105
It's still not too late.

90
00:08:00,103 --> 00:08:01,624
Granny Juu isn't doing well at all.

91
00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:04,714
She said she wanted to see you.

92
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:09,817
I'm not sure anymore

93
00:08:11,225 --> 00:08:13,627
if I was the one Mom wanted
to take care of Granny Juu.

94
00:08:26,384 --> 00:08:27,906
Hello, Leo. What's up?

95
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,861
DR. KRISTIN CHEEVASOPON
VETERINARIAN

96
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:39,620
Lynx,

97
00:08:40,743 --> 00:08:42,098
Granny Juu is very old now

98
00:08:42,393 --> 00:08:43,903
and her body is too weak

99
00:08:44,453 --> 00:08:46,020
so it didn't respond to the medication.

100
00:08:48,518 --> 00:08:49,518
So I think…

101
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:53,116
you should prepare for the worst.

102
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,812
Hey! Prepare for the worst?

103
00:08:56,651 --> 00:08:57,707
You're the vet.

104
00:08:57,924 --> 00:08:59,587
You're supposed to know how to treat her.

105
00:09:00,467 --> 00:09:03,018
Leo, calm down.

106
00:09:04,530 --> 00:09:05,716
If medication doesn't work,

107
00:09:06,032 --> 00:09:07,323
then operate or do something.

108
00:09:07,451 --> 00:09:08,939
Don't just tell us to prepare to lose her.

109
00:09:08,963 --> 00:09:10,181
How the hell could we do that?

110
00:09:12,413 --> 00:09:13,427
You come with me.

111
00:09:17,774 --> 00:09:19,614
Is there any other way to treat her?

112
00:09:22,006 --> 00:09:24,100
We could try another medication.

113
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:26,713
But no one can guarantee

114
00:09:26,947 --> 00:09:28,018
it'll work.

115
00:09:29,392 --> 00:09:31,016
I feel for Granny Juu

116
00:09:32,016 --> 00:09:33,813
because changing the medication

117
00:09:36,019 --> 00:09:37,883
will definitely put her
through a lot of pain.

118
00:09:41,174 --> 00:09:42,198
What did she say?

119
00:09:48,798 --> 00:09:49,798
She said…

120
00:09:53,192 --> 00:09:54,313
she wanted to see Je Meow.

121
00:09:59,642 --> 00:10:02,096
She probably forgot…

122
00:10:05,901 --> 00:10:07,006
that Je Meow is gone.

123
00:10:13,894 --> 00:10:14,894
Granny Juu.

124
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,112
Mom's resting here now.

125
00:10:22,290 --> 00:10:23,405
She said…

126
00:10:27,488 --> 00:10:28,513
she misses Je Meow.

127
00:10:33,422 --> 00:10:34,705
I miss her too.

128
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:40,608
She's tired now.

129
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:43,558
I think…

130
00:10:48,087 --> 00:10:49,508
she won't make it back to Bangkok.

131
00:10:55,526 --> 00:10:56,548
Grandma, Grandpa, hi.

132
00:10:56,588 --> 00:10:57,588
Hi, dear.

133
00:10:57,613 --> 00:10:58,613
Hi.

134
00:10:58,747 --> 00:11:02,008
Hey, Juu. We finally meet.

135
00:11:04,894 --> 00:11:05,997
Have you eaten?

136
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:06,999
Not yet.

137
00:11:07,062 --> 00:11:09,097
Don't worry. I've got food ready for you.

138
00:11:09,435 --> 00:11:10,506
Let me help you with that.

139
00:11:10,607 --> 00:11:11,647
Come on then.

140
00:11:14,029 --> 00:11:15,052
Grandpa Petch.

141
00:11:15,190 --> 00:11:16,190
Hm?

142
00:11:16,736 --> 00:11:17,805
I need your advice.

143
00:11:18,962 --> 00:11:19,962
What is it?

144
00:11:20,792 --> 00:11:22,350
I already passed on the power to Lynx.

145
00:11:23,819 --> 00:11:24,901
But I don't know why

146
00:11:25,562 --> 00:11:27,206
Lynx still cannot hear cats talking.

147
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:34,522
What Lynx has been through is complicated.

148
00:11:36,014 --> 00:11:37,792
Him living with the cats right now,

149
00:11:38,384 --> 00:11:39,488
I don't know if it's because he loves them,

150
00:11:39,512 --> 00:11:41,212
or because he feels guilty about his mom.

151
00:11:42,392 --> 00:11:43,597
But from what I've seen,

152
00:11:45,582 --> 00:11:46,984
I think it's because he loves them.

153
00:11:49,752 --> 00:11:51,398
Do you think Lynx feels the same way?

154
00:11:59,898 --> 00:12:01,103
Here you are.

155
00:12:09,216 --> 00:12:10,216
Lynx.

156
00:12:10,927 --> 00:12:14,700
Tiger told me
that your mom gave the café to Leo.

157
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:17,825
It's not surprising.

158
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,307
If Mom gave what she loved most
to someone,

159
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:26,596
she must have loved that person dearly.

160
00:12:27,988 --> 00:12:30,698
I don't know why she made that decision.

161
00:12:31,054 --> 00:12:32,398
But what I do know is

162
00:12:33,327 --> 00:12:36,011
she loved you the most, Lynx.

163
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:41,418
Did she tell you that?

164
00:12:43,269 --> 00:12:45,084
Lynx, I think you know

165
00:12:45,173 --> 00:12:47,112
that Grandpa can talk to cats.

166
00:12:48,507 --> 00:12:49,507
Yes.

167
00:12:50,232 --> 00:12:54,213
I don't have that special
power like he does.

168
00:12:54,753 --> 00:12:57,996
But when I look into those cats' eyes,

169
00:12:58,596 --> 00:12:59,911
and see what they are up to,

170
00:13:00,393 --> 00:13:03,298
I know instantly what they want to tell me.

171
00:13:07,513 --> 00:13:10,706
I can see what a kind heart you have.

172
00:13:11,106 --> 00:13:16,906
So I'm sure you were raised
with so much love, dear.

173
00:13:46,053 --> 00:13:47,186
You can play the piano too?

174
00:13:50,037 --> 00:13:51,860
I used to learn when I was
in elementary school.

175
00:13:51,884 --> 00:13:53,197
Every time I played,

176
00:13:54,236 --> 00:13:55,824
Granny Juu would jump up and bother me.

177
00:14:06,592 --> 00:14:07,714
How about we play together?

178
00:14:36,121 --> 00:14:37,121
Granny Juu,

179
00:14:37,778 --> 00:14:38,897
the song is over,

180
00:14:40,414 --> 00:14:41,616
why won't you come bother us?

181
00:14:55,595 --> 00:14:56,730
Let's play it one more time.

182
00:15:10,653 --> 00:15:12,602
It smells familiar here,
doesn't it, Granny Juu?

183
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,715
This is Meow's room.

184
00:15:18,489 --> 00:15:19,489
Hm?

185
00:15:25,344 --> 00:15:26,400
You're tired now, right?

186
00:15:27,534 --> 00:15:28,916
Rest easy, Granny Juu.

187
00:15:29,627 --> 00:15:31,907
We'll take care of Lynx for you.

188
00:15:34,109 --> 00:15:35,413
Look after Lynx for us too.

189
00:15:39,868 --> 00:15:41,113
Take care of him.

190
00:15:48,262 --> 00:15:49,262
Granny Juu.

191
00:15:50,886 --> 00:15:51,931
Do you remember this?

192
00:15:53,421 --> 00:15:54,695
You left it for me.

193
00:15:58,893 --> 00:16:00,051
I'm returning it to you now.

194
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:04,515
If you have any wish to make,

195
00:16:06,671 --> 00:16:07,698
you may do it now.

196
00:16:10,851 --> 00:16:12,023
Granny Juu said,

197
00:16:14,715 --> 00:16:16,100
she wished for your happiness.

198
00:16:22,442 --> 00:16:23,604
My happiness

199
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:26,230
is being with you.

200
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:31,216
Let's sleep here together.

201
00:16:49,569 --> 00:16:50,569
Granny Juu.

202
00:16:57,975 --> 00:16:58,975
Granny Juu.

203
00:16:59,371 --> 00:17:00,371
Granny…

204
00:17:19,197 --> 00:17:20,197
Granny Juu.

205
00:17:43,894 --> 00:17:46,551
FOREVER IN MEMORY

206
00:17:55,643 --> 00:17:57,992
MAY YOUR SOUL FIND ITS PEACEFUL PLACE.

207
00:17:59,421 --> 00:18:00,861
ALWAYS IN MY HEART

208
00:18:07,206 --> 00:18:08,489
Granny Juu.

209
00:18:09,237 --> 00:18:10,719
I've missed you so much.

210
00:18:10,744 --> 00:18:12,210
Let me get a good look at you.

211
00:18:31,238 --> 00:18:32,301
Have you been well?

212
00:18:36,521 --> 00:18:38,004
We haven't seen each other in so long

213
00:18:40,316 --> 00:18:41,960
and that's the best greeting you've got?

214
00:18:44,119 --> 00:18:45,156
Have you eaten?

215
00:18:45,637 --> 00:18:47,924
No, not that either.

216
00:18:48,946 --> 00:18:50,101
I've heard that one before.

217
00:18:53,461 --> 00:18:54,563
I'm sorry, sweetie.

218
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:56,013
For what?

219
00:18:58,247 --> 00:18:59,908
You didn't do anything wrong.

220
00:19:01,687 --> 00:19:03,015
You made the right call

221
00:19:04,384 --> 00:19:05,701
not handing everything to me.

222
00:19:08,413 --> 00:19:10,004
Out of all your kids,

223
00:19:12,973 --> 00:19:14,684
I'm probably the worst one.

224
00:19:14,798 --> 00:19:17,203
No, that's not it at all, Lynx.

225
00:19:17,492 --> 00:19:18,592
I'm sorry, Mom.

226
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:21,117
If I had a choice,

227
00:19:23,703 --> 00:19:25,815
I would have wanted you
to have a better son too.

228
00:19:28,122 --> 00:19:29,408
If I had a choice,

229
00:19:31,126 --> 00:19:33,715
I would have wanted my father
to have the son he always wanted.

230
00:19:37,214 --> 00:19:40,213
I did everything to make him accept me.

231
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:43,706
I was a good kid—stayed home,

232
00:19:44,734 --> 00:19:46,222
did everything he told me to.

233
00:19:50,099 --> 00:19:52,103
The one thing I was willing
to break with him over

234
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,408
was deciding to have you.

235
00:20:01,694 --> 00:20:06,217
If I had chosen the path
my father wanted for me,

236
00:20:08,195 --> 00:20:09,892
I never would have met you.

237
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:15,298
So I wanted you to choose
your own path, just like I did.

238
00:20:17,384 --> 00:20:18,421
Because I knew

239
00:20:21,186 --> 00:20:22,804
how proud it would be

240
00:20:24,183 --> 00:20:26,113
to choose the best thing for yourself.

241
00:20:34,681 --> 00:20:35,893
If I could choose,

242
00:20:40,311 --> 00:20:41,811
could I keep running the café?

243
00:20:44,022 --> 00:20:45,045
Of course, sweetie.

244
00:20:45,768 --> 00:20:46,808
You can do that

245
00:20:48,472 --> 00:20:49,954
because you genuinely love the cats.

246
00:20:59,801 --> 00:21:00,801
Mom.

247
00:21:03,782 --> 00:21:04,788
Do you love me?

248
00:21:11,368 --> 00:21:13,214
I made you wake up early,

249
00:21:14,087 --> 00:21:15,896
and go through the same old routines,

250
00:21:18,588 --> 00:21:20,521
and put up with me every day.

251
00:21:21,331 --> 00:21:22,503
No matter how stubborn I was,

252
00:21:23,184 --> 00:21:25,250
no matter how many times
I turned a deaf ear to you,

253
00:21:26,097 --> 00:21:27,802
you were still there for me.

254
00:21:30,451 --> 00:21:32,230
Even though you never said it out loud,

255
00:21:34,437 --> 00:21:35,797
everything you did for me

256
00:21:37,348 --> 00:21:38,823
was your way of saying you loved me.

257
00:21:47,695 --> 00:21:48,695
Then,

258
00:21:50,441 --> 00:21:51,441
I think…

259
00:21:53,390 --> 00:21:54,714
I must truly love the cats too.

260
00:21:57,285 --> 00:21:58,401
I love you, Lynx.

261
00:22:04,161 --> 00:22:05,161
I love you.

262
00:22:05,329 --> 00:22:07,106
I love you too.

263
00:22:11,577 --> 00:22:12,577
I knew.

264
00:22:14,824 --> 00:22:17,886
I saw everything you did.

265
00:22:19,634 --> 00:22:22,325
Granny Juu praised you to me every night.

266
00:22:23,209 --> 00:22:25,102
I'm so proud of you, you know?

267
00:22:26,644 --> 00:22:29,697
I'm proud to be your mother.

268
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:35,087
I'm proud to have raised you
into such a good man.

269
00:22:37,050 --> 00:22:41,807
And I'm proudest of all
to have been your mother

270
00:22:42,443 --> 00:22:44,908
until the very last second of my life.

271
00:22:51,217 --> 00:22:52,958
You're the best.

272
00:22:54,626 --> 00:22:58,538
It's not too late for
me to say that, right?

273
00:23:16,489 --> 00:23:17,849
I have to go now.

274
00:23:19,102 --> 00:23:21,303
We'll see each other again someday.

275
00:23:21,677 --> 00:23:23,697
No matter where or when,

276
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:27,125
I'll be waiting to hold
you like this again.

277
00:23:30,324 --> 00:23:31,324
Okay?

278
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:41,807
See you, sweetie.

279
00:23:41,995 --> 00:23:42,856
Can you not go?

280
00:23:42,881 --> 00:23:43,896
See you again.

281
00:23:43,972 --> 00:23:45,504
Can you not go?

282
00:25:00,441 --> 00:25:01,441
Lynx.

283
00:25:06,456 --> 00:25:07,456
Granny Juu.

284
00:25:11,891 --> 00:25:12,891
Granny Juu.

285
00:25:13,754 --> 00:25:14,754
(Lynx…)

286
00:25:17,702 --> 00:25:20,513
(Remember the first day we met?)

287
00:25:20,912 --> 00:25:24,117
(You promised to take the best care of me.)

288
00:25:26,164 --> 00:25:29,096
(Thank you for keeping your promise.)

289
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:35,602
(See you again.)

290
00:25:38,226 --> 00:25:39,595
Granny Juu said...

291
00:25:41,742 --> 00:25:42,835
See you, Granny Juu.

292
00:25:43,064 --> 00:25:48,402
♪ I told you I love you, love you ♪

293
00:25:49,162 --> 00:25:54,478
♪ Since the first day I laid eyes on you ♪

294
00:25:55,014 --> 00:26:00,617
♪ Even though my voice can't be heard ♪

295
00:26:01,023 --> 00:26:06,682
♪ But someday you'll
understand every word ♪

296
00:26:07,445 --> 00:26:10,828
♪ Every word ♪

297
00:26:18,925 --> 00:26:20,817
When I was little,
whenever I played the piano,

298
00:26:22,499 --> 00:26:25,211
Granny Juu would always jump up
and curl on my lap.

299
00:26:28,579 --> 00:26:32,512
She must have loved listening to me play.

300
00:26:35,737 --> 00:26:37,916
And Mom would always praise me

301
00:26:39,404 --> 00:26:40,508
for playing beautifully,

302
00:26:43,011 --> 00:26:45,129
even though I always hit the wrong notes.

303
00:26:46,133 --> 00:26:49,197
I think that was her way of saying
I love you without the word "love."

304
00:26:56,521 --> 00:27:01,014
So I think there's nothing better

305
00:27:02,799 --> 00:27:05,199
to send off Mom and Granny Juu than…

306
00:27:07,434 --> 00:27:08,510
than this.

307
00:27:14,392 --> 00:27:15,392
Mom,

308
00:27:16,448 --> 00:27:17,448
Granny Juu,

309
00:27:19,934 --> 00:27:21,194
come listen to this song, okay?

310
00:27:57,801 --> 00:28:02,513
♪ Everything has reached its end ♪

311
00:28:03,669 --> 00:28:07,875
♪ I must face the truth ♪

312
00:28:09,219 --> 00:28:13,838
♪ That's piercing through my heart ♪

313
00:28:16,942 --> 00:28:20,616
♪ I miss you ♪

314
00:28:21,303 --> 00:28:25,088
♪ I miss the light within your smile ♪

315
00:28:27,111 --> 00:28:31,022
♪ Just when I looked into your eyes ♪

316
00:28:32,913 --> 00:28:37,487
♪ Just when our eyes met ♪

317
00:28:39,592 --> 00:28:45,086
♪ No matter how deep
the pain tearing my mind ♪

318
00:28:45,419 --> 00:28:51,776
♪ No matter how much hurt I hold inside ♪

319
00:28:52,406 --> 00:28:57,642
♪ This is as far as I can walk with you ♪

320
00:28:58,249 --> 00:29:03,018
♪ Even as every part of
me wants to hold you tight ♪

321
00:29:03,723 --> 00:29:06,148
♪ Goodbye ♪

322
00:29:06,620 --> 00:29:12,505
♪ Goodbye, my love ♪

323
00:29:15,757 --> 00:29:21,012
♪ I wish I could speak every word of love ♪

324
00:29:21,653 --> 00:29:26,442
♪ But all I can do is let you go ♪

325
00:29:27,176 --> 00:29:29,500
♪ Goodbye ♪

326
00:29:30,095 --> 00:29:37,046
♪ Goodbye, farewell to you ♪

327
00:29:38,879 --> 00:29:46,876
♪ Though the days we
had will never return ♪

328
00:29:49,081 --> 00:29:52,975
♪ I must accept ♪

329
00:29:54,547 --> 00:29:59,628
♪ That the time has come ♪

330
00:30:01,546 --> 00:30:06,982
♪ No matter how deep
the pain tearing my mind ♪

331
00:30:07,367 --> 00:30:13,347
♪ No matter how much hurt I hold inside ♪

332
00:30:14,014 --> 00:30:19,638
♪ This is as far as I can walk with you ♪

333
00:30:20,211 --> 00:30:25,104
♪ Even as every part of
me wants to hold you tight ♪

334
00:30:25,654 --> 00:30:28,025
♪ Goodbye ♪

335
00:30:28,629 --> 00:30:34,438
♪ Goodbye, my love ♪

336
00:30:37,678 --> 00:30:42,946
♪ I wish I could speak every word of love ♪

337
00:30:43,571 --> 00:30:48,561
♪ But all I can do is let you go ♪

338
00:30:49,118 --> 00:30:51,464
♪ Goodbye ♪

339
00:30:52,064 --> 00:30:58,716
♪ Goodbye, farewell to you ♪

340
00:31:01,152 --> 00:31:06,404
♪ This is as far as I can walk with you ♪

341
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:12,047
♪ Even as every part of
me wants to hold you tight ♪

342
00:31:12,499 --> 00:31:14,882
♪ Goodbye ♪

343
00:31:15,422 --> 00:31:21,251
♪ Goodbye, my love ♪

344
00:31:24,504 --> 00:31:29,824
♪ I wish I could speak every word of love ♪

345
00:31:30,319 --> 00:31:35,171
♪ But all I can do is let you go ♪

346
00:31:35,940 --> 00:31:38,308
♪ Goodbye ♪

347
00:31:38,838 --> 00:31:45,833
♪ Goodbye, farewell to you ♪

348
00:31:48,035 --> 00:31:50,286
Lynx, I'm sorry.

349
00:31:51,859 --> 00:31:53,314
I rented you a new gown, right?

350
00:31:54,519 --> 00:31:56,423
Granny Juu, tell Lynx to smile.

351
00:31:56,716 --> 00:31:58,526
Smile, Lynx.

352
00:32:11,281 --> 00:32:13,273
♪ Goodbye ♪

353
00:32:14,022 --> 00:32:19,065
♪ Goodbye, farewell to you ♪

354
00:32:39,887 --> 00:32:40,887
Hey.

355
00:32:41,398 --> 00:32:42,407
You're still here?

356
00:32:44,321 --> 00:32:45,790
I worried the cats might get lonely.

357
00:32:46,519 --> 00:32:48,119
So I wanted to stay and comfort them.

358
00:32:49,304 --> 00:32:50,824
I already took my allergy pill though.

359
00:32:50,873 --> 00:32:51,891
(Don't believe him.)

360
00:32:52,096 --> 00:32:55,624
(He just said he missed Granny Juu
and didn't want to sleep alone.)

361
00:32:58,053 --> 00:32:59,308
I can hear them now, you know.

362
00:33:00,482 --> 00:33:01,711
You're down here

363
00:33:02,405 --> 00:33:04,005
because you miss her too, right?

364
00:33:05,803 --> 00:33:06,803
Mm…

365
00:33:10,061 --> 00:33:11,061
At least,

366
00:33:12,022 --> 00:33:13,793
Granny Juu's scent is still in here.

367
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:21,008
Hey, where's the blanket we wrapped her in?

368
00:33:22,912 --> 00:33:24,312
It was still here this morning.

369
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:26,545
It's here.

370
00:33:29,688 --> 00:33:30,800
I took it to my room.

371
00:33:31,528 --> 00:33:32,623
Then I realized,

372
00:33:33,819 --> 00:33:36,715
I couldn't be the only one missing her.

373
00:33:44,891 --> 00:33:46,217
How about tonight

374
00:33:47,545 --> 00:33:49,398
we all sleep in here together?

375
00:34:00,073 --> 00:34:01,820
Before, this blanket only had Mom's scent.

376
00:34:03,262 --> 00:34:05,223
Now Granny Juu's scent is in it too.

377
00:34:09,914 --> 00:34:11,306
The night Granny Juu was gone,

378
00:34:14,215 --> 00:34:15,322
I dreamed of Mom, you know.

379
00:34:18,558 --> 00:34:19,708
I dreamed that I graduated

380
00:34:23,051 --> 00:34:24,924
and Mom was there
to take my graduation photos.

381
00:34:26,163 --> 00:34:27,812
I actually had a dream that night too.

382
00:34:31,823 --> 00:34:33,492
I dreamed that Je Meow came to thank me.

383
00:34:37,287 --> 00:34:39,797
But she didn't say
what she was thanking me for.

384
00:34:42,249 --> 00:34:43,265
What about you?

385
00:34:44,690 --> 00:34:45,756
Did you dream of her too?

386
00:34:55,226 --> 00:34:56,237
No, I didn't.

387
00:34:59,193 --> 00:35:00,204
Go to sleep already.

388
00:35:03,026 --> 00:35:04,026
Tomorrow…

389
00:35:06,146 --> 00:35:08,004
I have to wake up early and open the café.

390
00:35:42,118 --> 00:35:44,605
Hey! Don't take the whole blanket.

391
00:35:46,488 --> 00:35:48,210
Leo. Share it too.

392
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:51,453
No.

393
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,462
Come on. Share it too.

394
00:36:00,558 --> 00:36:03,960
(For me, that night wasn't a dream.)

395
00:36:05,100 --> 00:36:06,102
(Right, Mom?)

396
00:36:09,382 --> 00:36:12,828
1 YEAR LATER

397
00:36:13,104 --> 00:36:16,906
Alright everyone,
back to your posts, like always.

398
00:36:17,717 --> 00:36:18,911
And one more thing…

399
00:36:19,862 --> 00:36:23,090
Jumbo is a big boy now.

400
00:36:25,383 --> 00:36:26,624
Do you even realize that, huh?

401
00:36:31,027 --> 00:36:34,780
♪ Meow Meow Meow Meow Meow ♪

402
00:36:35,080 --> 00:36:38,314
♪ Meow Meow Meow Meow Meow ♪

403
00:36:38,769 --> 00:36:42,258
♪ Meow Meow Meow Meow Meow ♪

404
00:36:44,536 --> 00:36:46,405
Happy birthday, Jumbo.

405
00:36:52,909 --> 00:36:56,408
Who do you think
our first customer today will be?

406
00:37:05,009 --> 00:37:08,788
(It's been a year
since you took Granny Juu with you.)

407
00:37:09,847 --> 00:37:12,927
(Even though it feels a little lonely,
we're all doing well.)

408
00:37:13,836 --> 00:37:14,856
(Krapor…)

409
00:37:15,163 --> 00:37:17,811
(no, I should call him Daddy Krapor now.)

410
00:37:18,122 --> 00:37:21,210
(He won big on the lottery
with Granny Juu's age numbers.)

411
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:22,440
Look!

412
00:37:22,493 --> 00:37:25,818
Don't call me Sugar Daddy,
call me the man devoted to love.

413
00:37:25,924 --> 00:37:28,932
Which one do you like?
Take your pick, my Jenny.

414
00:37:31,832 --> 00:37:32,981
You should leave now.

415
00:37:33,769 --> 00:37:35,192
Just a little longer.

416
00:37:35,394 --> 00:37:38,116
(As for Dr. Pom, he's going to
study abroad to specialize further.)

417
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:41,216
(He wants cats to live longer
and stay healthy as long as possible.)

418
00:37:41,681 --> 00:37:43,605
(So Dr. Pug is taking over the clinic.)

419
00:37:43,902 --> 00:37:46,998
(As for Jumbo's grandpa and grandma,
they're still very much fond of him.)

420
00:37:47,878 --> 00:37:49,981
I'm giving this room to you, Jumbo.

421
00:37:50,048 --> 00:37:51,501
No one else is sharing it with you.

422
00:37:51,550 --> 00:37:54,701
The former owner has moved out
to live with his boyfriend.

423
00:37:54,779 --> 00:37:56,706
If this isn't enough, you let Grandpa know.

424
00:37:57,032 --> 00:37:58,906
I've got a hundred Rai of land.

425
00:37:58,962 --> 00:38:01,223
Whatever you want, just say the word.

426
00:38:01,464 --> 00:38:03,024
Am I not your son, Pa?

427
00:38:03,158 --> 00:38:04,278
Nom, nom, kid.

428
00:38:04,959 --> 00:38:07,217
We've got our grandkid now.
You don't matter anymore.

429
00:38:08,970 --> 00:38:10,376
(As for Grandpa Petch and Grand Ma Tam, )

430
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:12,266
(they taught me how to make
Korat fried noodles, )

431
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:13,773
(just like they once taught you.)

432
00:38:19,407 --> 00:38:20,450
Is it good, P'Tiger?

433
00:38:24,453 --> 00:38:28,002
(And my rascal brother, he's been trying
to finish up his college credits, )

434
00:38:28,488 --> 00:38:32,785
(but it seems to be going well
because he's got himself a great tutor.)

435
00:38:33,690 --> 00:38:34,721
Did you get it?

436
00:38:36,776 --> 00:38:37,918
If you pass this semester,

437
00:38:38,241 --> 00:38:39,901
I'll let you ask for anything. One thing.

438
00:38:41,629 --> 00:38:42,831
Can I be your boyfriend then?

439
00:38:51,705 --> 00:38:53,013
You said anything, didn't you?

440
00:38:53,309 --> 00:38:54,485
You're not so bold after all.

441
00:38:57,396 --> 00:38:58,407
Pass your exams first.

442
00:38:58,824 --> 00:39:00,044
Then I'll be your boyfriend.

443
00:39:01,893 --> 00:39:02,992
I'll give it my all.

444
00:39:04,571 --> 00:39:07,918
(As for the cats' dad,
he's fully recovered from his allergies.)

445
00:39:11,009 --> 00:39:13,527
(Well, almost.)

446
00:39:14,229 --> 00:39:17,278
(Soon, he'll get to hold cats
to his heart's content)

447
00:39:17,790 --> 00:39:19,521
(without sneezing or coughing.)

448
00:39:21,172 --> 00:39:23,597
(I'm now a full-time papa, )

449
00:39:23,927 --> 00:39:26,906
(taking care of the kids
and bringing happiness to every customer, )

450
00:39:27,084 --> 00:39:28,222
(just like you did.)

451
00:39:28,829 --> 00:39:29,832
(I miss you, Mom.)

452
00:39:30,257 --> 00:39:34,606
(I guess you're scratching
Granny Juu's belly somewhere.)

453
00:39:34,796 --> 00:39:37,122
(I now have to go get my cat fix too.)

454
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:38,617
(Love you, Mom.)

455
00:39:38,882 --> 00:39:39,882
Lynx,

456
00:39:42,914 --> 00:39:44,011
do you have plans tonight?

457
00:39:45,820 --> 00:39:46,820
Why?

458
00:39:48,023 --> 00:39:49,223
Wanna go see cats in my room?

459
00:40:22,034 --> 00:40:23,034
Ouch.

460
00:40:25,052 --> 00:40:26,220
Are you a cat?

461
00:40:26,949 --> 00:40:28,362
You never miss a chance to bite me.

462
00:40:28,839 --> 00:40:30,015
I'm not a cat.

463
00:41:11,704 --> 00:41:14,904
Hey. You're nudging me
under the blanket this early?

464
00:41:16,294 --> 00:41:19,397
The scratch from last night
still hasn't healed, you know.

465
00:41:21,541 --> 00:41:22,700
That wasn't me.

466
00:41:24,432 --> 00:41:25,432
Then who?

467
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:27,291
(It was me!)

468
00:41:27,316 --> 00:41:28,316
Jumbo!

469
00:41:28,341 --> 00:41:32,037
(You dads still have your balls.
(That means you can have more kids.)

470
00:41:34,792 --> 00:41:35,970
Jumbo, we…

471
00:41:36,016 --> 00:41:39,797
(Jumbo wants little kitties.
(Can you dads make kitties for me?)

472
00:41:48,446 --> 00:41:50,511
We can barely handle the cats we have now.

473
00:41:51,019 --> 00:41:52,218
Why bother getting more?

474
00:41:53,756 --> 00:41:56,033
But I think I understand Jumbo.

475
00:41:57,915 --> 00:42:00,089
When I was little, I used to ask my mom
for a little sibling too.

476
00:42:00,113 --> 00:42:02,812
Don't you remember how troublesome
a young cat is?

477
00:42:04,394 --> 00:42:05,810
Running wild all over the house.

478
00:42:06,433 --> 00:42:07,881
Never listening to anything you say.

479
00:42:08,236 --> 00:42:10,120
And always bringing
you the strangest things.

480
00:42:10,246 --> 00:42:12,065
And whenever he picked a fight
with a bigger cat and lost,

481
00:42:12,089 --> 00:42:13,542
he'd always run and hide behind you.

482
00:42:22,737 --> 00:42:23,737
Lynx.

483
00:42:25,285 --> 00:42:26,320
That's food for young cats.

484
00:42:28,503 --> 00:42:31,897
I totally forgot we don't have
a young cat anymore.

485
00:42:35,605 --> 00:42:36,817
Whenever Jumbo gets scolded,

486
00:42:37,303 --> 00:42:39,364
he gives you those big innocent eyes
just like this.

487
00:42:40,816 --> 00:42:44,297
In that case,
let's go find Jumbo a little sibling.

488
00:42:50,936 --> 00:42:54,214
I think we should start by looking in
cat adoption groups.

489
00:42:55,138 --> 00:42:56,332
Good idea.

490
00:42:57,114 --> 00:42:58,314
But if we can't find one,

491
00:42:58,576 --> 00:42:59,913
we can always check pet stores.

492
00:43:04,653 --> 00:43:06,051
Lynx, look.

493
00:43:07,033 --> 00:43:08,105
You're incredibly fast.

494
00:43:10,707 --> 00:43:12,888
Aw, really cute.

495
00:43:15,198 --> 00:43:17,203
Look at that belly. Who could resist?

496
00:43:17,454 --> 00:43:21,100
But I don't think it'll
be easy to find one.

497
00:43:23,051 --> 00:43:26,122
What criteria did your mom usually use
when choosing a cat for the café?

498
00:43:27,116 --> 00:43:30,602
Mom said to leave it up to fate.

499
00:43:32,265 --> 00:43:35,216
In that case, let's skip ahead to naming.

500
00:43:36,422 --> 00:43:38,910
All our cats' names
start with Jor-Jan in Thai.

501
00:43:39,716 --> 00:43:40,910
Dad's name is Tiger.

502
00:43:41,226 --> 00:43:42,412
Papa's name is Lynx.

503
00:43:43,703 --> 00:43:45,508
The kid should be named…

504
00:43:47,247 --> 00:43:48,247
Jinx!

505
00:43:50,265 --> 00:43:51,617
That means bad luck in English.

506
00:43:54,148 --> 00:43:58,145
Then… Jiger.

507
00:43:59,733 --> 00:44:00,916
You're going too far.

508
00:44:01,576 --> 00:44:03,021
Our kid will definitely get teased.

509
00:44:06,571 --> 00:44:09,801
It has to start with Jor-Jan
and have a good meaning.

510
00:44:16,355 --> 00:44:18,690
Leo, what are you doing?

511
00:44:19,204 --> 00:44:21,406
Have you unloaded all
the cats from your car?

512
00:44:21,689 --> 00:44:23,588
I think I hear a cat in your car.

513
00:44:23,676 --> 00:44:25,728
(Help me. Help me, please.)

514
00:44:25,761 --> 00:44:27,797
(I'm in here. Help me.)

515
00:44:38,692 --> 00:44:39,701
I looked everywhere.

516
00:44:41,568 --> 00:44:42,793
Are you sure it's in the car?

517
00:44:47,727 --> 00:44:51,251
(Help me. I can't get
out. I'm trapped in here.)

518
00:44:51,381 --> 00:44:52,841
(I'm trapped in here.)

519
00:44:55,671 --> 00:44:58,607
Hey, what are you doing in there?

520
00:44:59,073 --> 00:45:00,073
Hm?

521
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:01,933
I remember now.

522
00:45:02,229 --> 00:45:04,716
The other day I saw a mama cat
carrying a kitten in her mouth.

523
00:45:04,807 --> 00:45:05,822
This must be that kitten.

524
00:45:07,995 --> 00:45:10,597
So you got in there to stay warm?
Don't be scared.

525
00:45:10,897 --> 00:45:13,805
How about I take a picture
and post it on our fan page?

526
00:45:14,132 --> 00:45:15,488
Someone might want to adopt it.

527
00:45:19,404 --> 00:45:20,404
Lynx…

528
00:45:22,632 --> 00:45:23,908
can I hold it?

529
00:45:24,959 --> 00:45:26,000
What about your allergies?

530
00:45:53,614 --> 00:45:54,828
Are you having a reaction now?

531
00:45:56,201 --> 00:45:57,201
No.

532
00:45:59,331 --> 00:46:00,451
I'm just happy

533
00:46:03,598 --> 00:46:05,115
that I finally got over my allergies.

534
00:46:13,060 --> 00:46:17,224
Wanna stay with us, Giant.

535
00:46:17,558 --> 00:46:18,637
(Giant?)

536
00:46:18,670 --> 00:46:19,428
What do you say?

537
00:46:19,453 --> 00:46:22,606
(I like this name. Can
I stay here with you?)

538
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:33,316
MONTHS LATER

539
00:46:33,372 --> 00:46:34,372
Ready, guys?

540
00:46:39,773 --> 00:46:40,817
Wait for me too!

541
00:46:42,844 --> 00:46:44,540
How can you take a group photo without me?

542
00:46:44,894 --> 00:46:45,617
Congrats.

543
00:46:45,672 --> 00:46:47,106
Hurry up, the timer's running out!

544
00:47:24,336 --> 00:47:26,720
Cat-Cheer Café, welcome.

545
00:47:44,829 --> 00:47:46,509
I've signed them all.

546
00:47:47,206 --> 00:47:48,404
Just need your signature now.

547
00:47:53,778 --> 00:47:58,126
Now, all debts between us are settled.

548
00:48:01,887 --> 00:48:02,887
Not yet.

549
00:48:04,283 --> 00:48:05,655
There's another set of documents.

550
00:48:08,696 --> 00:48:09,696
Which one?

551
00:48:10,882 --> 00:48:12,312
Didn't you always complain

552
00:48:13,181 --> 00:48:16,907
that we'd been together so long,
why weren't we official yet?

553
00:48:20,403 --> 00:48:23,012
Well, here you go. I took care of it.

554
00:48:24,107 --> 00:48:25,147
Lynx's ready.

555
00:48:25,751 --> 00:48:26,826
So are the witnesses.

556
00:48:27,514 --> 00:48:28,581
Only you now, Tiger.

557
00:48:28,626 --> 00:48:29,671
Are you ready?

558
00:48:32,041 --> 00:48:34,183
I've been ready even before
Dr. Pom started speaking.

559
00:48:38,972 --> 00:48:39,622
Hello.

560
00:48:39,663 --> 00:48:41,222
Hello.

561
00:48:41,502 --> 00:48:42,506
Please have a seat.

562
00:48:59,311 --> 00:49:00,320
Congratulations.

563
00:49:00,460 --> 00:49:01,460
Thank you.

564
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:05,102
MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE MR. THATCHAKORN
ARANYASIRI AND MR. ASHIRA VILAWONG

565
00:49:14,869 --> 00:49:17,208
Now you're my debtor.

566
00:49:17,738 --> 00:49:20,725
Now you're my servant.

567
00:49:24,377 --> 00:49:25,811
If you break the contract,

568
00:49:28,936 --> 00:49:30,302
don't say I didn't warn you.
